Fuel stop requirements add another variable to route selection and timing. Shuttle companies operating large vehicles must plan fuel stops based on passenger load, weather conditions, and available fuel station locations. These stops typically add 10-15 minutes to travel time but become necessary for longer routes or when carrying full passenger loads.

